<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="155" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,654,2013]" pageId="3" pageNumber="155">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1951,1977]" pageId="3" pageNumber="155">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific name is derived from the Latin word: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liao, Chen &amp; Li" authorityYear="2022" box="[914,1012,1951,1976]" class="Insecta" family="Tiphiidae" genus="Hylomesa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="155" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctata">
<emphasis box="[914,1012,1951,1976]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="155">punctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= punctured), referring to dorsum of propodeum and vertex anteriorly with dense punctures.
</paragraph>
